</refnamediv>
<!-- body begins here -->
<refsynopsisdiv id='synopsis'>
<para>source &lt;(npm completion)</para>
</refsynopsisdiv>


<refsect1 id='description'><title>DESCRIPTION</title>
<para>Enables tab-completion in all npm commands.</para>

<para>The synopsis above
loads the completions into your current shell.  Adding it to
your ~/.bashrc or ~/.zshrc will make the completions available
everywhere:</para>

<literallayout remap='.nf'>
npm completion &gt;&gt; ~/.bashrc
npm completion &gt;&gt; ~/.zshrc
</literallayout> <!-- .fi -->

<para>You may of course also pipe the output of npm completion to a file
such as <filename>/usr/local/etc/bash_completion.d/npm</filename> if you have a system
that will read that file for you.</para>

<para>When <emphasis remap='B'>COMP_CWORD</emphasis>, <emphasis remap='B'>COMP_LINE</emphasis>, and <emphasis remap='B'>COMP_POINT</emphasis> are defined in the
environment, <emphasis remap='B'>npm completion</emphasis> acts in "plumbing mode", and outputs
completions based on the arguments.</para>
</refsect1>

